        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:96:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/96/5466",
        "text": [
          " :\nقُلْتُ لَهُ اَلرَّجُلُ يَكُونُ لَهُ اَلْوَلَدُ يَسَعُهُ أَنْ يَجْعَلَ مَالَهُ لِقَرَابَتِهِ قَالَ \"هُوَ مَالُهُ يَصْنَعُ بِهِ مَا شَاءَ إِلَى أَنْ يَأْتِيَهُ اَلْمَوْتُ\"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5466 - Abdullah ibn Jabalah narrated from Samaah, from Abu Baṣir, from Abu Abdullah Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) who said:\nI asked Imam (as), \"A man who has children, is it permissible for him to give his wealth to his relatives?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"It is his wealth; he may do with it as he wishes until death comes to him.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2462,
        "local_index": 2,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "5467 - وَ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "تَصْدِيقُ ذَلِكَ- مَا رَوَاهُ صَفْوَانُ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "narrator",
              "path": "/people/narrators/314",
              "text": "مُرَازِمٍ‌"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " فِي"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:96:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/96/5467",
        "text": [
          " الرَّجُلِ يُعْطِي الشَّيْ‌ءَ مِنْ مَالِهِ فِي مَرَضِهِ قَالَ إِذَا أَبَانَ بِهِ فَهُوَ جَائِزٌ وَ إِنْ أَوْصَى بِهِ فَمِنَ الثُّلُثِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5467 - And the confirmation of this is what Ṣafwan narrated from Murazim regarding a man who gives something from his wealth during his illness.\nImm (as) said: \"If he clearly transfers it (during his lifetime), then it is valid. However, if he bequeaths it (for after his death), then it is only from one-third of his wealth.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2463,
        "local_index": 3,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "5468 - وَ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "أَمَّا حَدِيثُ عَلِيِّ بْنِ أَسْبَاطٍ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "narrator",
              "path": "/people/narrators/197",
              "text": "ثَعْلَبَةَ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "أَبِي اَلْحَسَنِ عَمْرِو بْنِ شَدَّادٍ اَلْأَزْدِيِّ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "narrator",
              "path": "/people/narrators/210",
              "text": "عَمَّارِ بْنِ مُوسَى"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "أَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:96:3",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/96/5468",
        "text": [
          ":\n\"اَلرَّجُلُ أَحَقُّ بِمَالِهِ مَا دَامَ فِيهِ اَلرُّوحُ إِنْ أَوْصَى بِهِ كُلِّهِ فَهُوَ جَائِزٌ لَهُ\"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5468 - As for the narration of Ali ibn Asbaṭ from Thaʿlabah from Abu Al-Hasan Amr ibn Shaddad Al-Azdi from Ammar ibn Musa from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"A man has the most right over his wealth as long as his soul remains in him. If he bequeaths all of it, it is permissible for him.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2464,
        "local_index": 4,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "5469 - وَ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "تَصْدِيقُ ذَلِكَ مَا رَوَاهُ إِسْمَاعِيلُ بْنُ أَبِي زِيَادٍ اَلسَّكُونِيُّ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "narrator",
              "path": "/people/narrators/208",
              "text": "جَعْفَرِ بْنِ مُحَمَّدٍ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "أَبِيهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : أَنَّهُ سُئِلَ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنِ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "اَلرَّجُلِ يَمُوتُ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " وَ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "لاَ وَارِثَ لَهُ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " وَ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "لاَ عَصَبَةَ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:96:4",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/96/5469",
        "text": [
          " \"يُوصِي بِمَالِهِ حَيْثُ يَشَاءُ فِي اَلْمُسْلِمِينَ وَ اَلْمَسَاكِينِ وَ اِبْنِ اَلسَّبِيلِ\"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5469 - And a confirmation of this is what was narrated by Ismaʿil ibn Abi Ziyad Al-Sakuni from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Abu Abdullah Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), that he was asked about a man who dies without leaving behind an heir or any male relative (Aṣabah).\nImam (as) said: \"He may bequeath his wealth as he wishes among the Muslims, the poor, and the wayfarer.\""
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  },
